___Haskell Mode___
C-c C-l load the current file into ghci

___Prolog mode___

C-c C-b        Consult the current buffer.
C-c Ret        Start prolog runtime.

___C mode___

M-x compile    Compile using make.
C-c C-e        ''
C-x `          Visit the next error raised by compile.
C-u C-x C-`    Go back to the start of the errors.

___Erlang mode___

C-c C-k (erlang-compile) - Compiles the Erlang module in the current buffer. 

C-x` (erlang-next-error) - Move the point on to the next error.

C-c C-a (erlang-align-arrows) - Line up arrows 

___ Misc ___

Set background transparent
M-x ns-set-background-alpha 0.8

Quit partially entered commands
C-g

___SLIME Lisp Mode___

C-c C-k (slime-compile-and-load-file) - Compile and load the current buffer's source file. 
C-c M-k (slime-compile-file) - Compile (but don't load) the current buffer's source file. 
C-c C-c (slime-compile-defun) - Compile the top-level form at point.

___Ruby Mode___
M-x describe-mode
C-c C-s (run-ruby) - Start ruby runtime.

__Python Mode__
C-c C-l

__ETAGS __
M-.       goes to the symbol definition
M-0 M-.   goes to the next matching definition
M-*       return to your starting point
M-x tags-search <type your regexp>       initiate a search
M-,                                      go to the next match

__ Switch Window
C-x o Select another window (other-window). That is o, not zero.
C-x 2 Split window vertically
C-x 3 Split window horizontally


